**Why Relationships Matter**
- Friends and family support you
- Connections reduce loneliness
- Relationships help you feel normal
- Support makes caregiving easier

**Challenges Caregivers Face**
- Less time for others
- Feeling too tired to socialize
- Friends may not understand
- Guilt about taking time away
- Relationship with care recipient changing

**Keeping Your Marriage/Partnership Strong**
- Schedule time together
- Talk about things besides caregiving
- Share the load when possible
- Stay physically affectionate
- Communicate openly about stress

**Staying Connected with Friends**
- Accept that contact may be less frequent
- Be honest about your situation
- Say yes to invitations when you can
- Use technology to stay in touch
- Let friends help with caregiving

**Maintaining Family Ties**
- Include family in care discussions
- Ask relatives to visit
- Share caregiving responsibilities
- Keep communication open
- Do not isolate yourself

**Tips That Help**
- Put social time on your calendar
- Even 15 minutes counts
- Quality over quantity
- Let go of guilt
- Accept that relationships may change`,
